The paper deals with the construction of a geometric spanner, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic aspects of the construction involve data structures and graph algorithms (cs.DS), and the analysis of the expected construction time involves probabilistic methods (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of linear programming and optimization techniques (cs.NA) in the analysis. Finally, the practical applications of geometric spanners in network design and communication protocols fall under the category of systems and networking (cs.SI).
